   Instead of naming all functions as `RunMain`, I recommend to use a representative name as if it was part of "real" code. Also, maybe some of the `RunMain` could be split into multiple functions, like a: `MakeArrays()`, `MakeTableFromChunks()`. But not sure how the return value would look like for a collection of items. Arrow has `Result` which can be a value or a `Status`, but I do not think it handles sequences.

